 matters. The Feminine Gaze: A Canadian Compendium of Non-Fiction Women Authors and Their Books, 1836-1945 will be an invaluable research tool for women’s studies and for all who wish to supplement the male gaze on Canada’s past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian prose literaturexBibliographyxWomen authors. 0aCanadian prose literaturexWomen authorsvBibliography. 0aWomen authors, CanadianvBio-bibliographyvDictionaries. 0aWomen authors, CanadianvBio-bibliography. 0aWomen authors, CanadianvBiographyvDictionaries. 0aWomen authors, CanadianxBio-bibliography. 0aWomen authors, Canadiany19th centuryvBiography. 0aWomen authors, Canadiany20th centuryvBiography. 4aLiterary Criticism. 4aLiterary Criticism: Canadian Literature. 4aSocial Science: Women’s Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920845240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889208452423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889208452/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles